This paper proposes an approach to learning agents for active robotic mapping, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The approach uses deep reinforcement learning, which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of sensor models, which suggests that computer vision (cs.CV) may be relevant. Finally, the approach involves optimizing exploration policies, which could be considered a control systems (cs.SY) problem.
